            This is an interactive prototype meant for documentation. We wanted to see if it is
            possible (and feasible) to create a documentation template in the same figma file.
            In this document we'll be discussing how to use this template.
          %h3.documentation-sub-header.mt-6
            Quick Start
          %p.mt-2
            When you duplicate this file from community, select all the elements and copy-paste
            them into your design file. This way you can also copy the Master Components and use
            them however you like. You can also apply your own styles on Master Components to
            make it consistent with your design or leave it as it is.
          .color-note{ class: "bg-bg-purple-1/50" }
            = image_tag "info_icon.svg"
            %p
              We will only show an example to showcase this template. Feel free to add your own
              creativity and share remixes in Figma Community.
          %h3.documentation-sub-header.mt-7
            Navigation
